//-->
</script>
<script type="text/javascript"
src="http://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/show_ads.js">
</script></div> <br></dl><br></dd><br><dd>the forgiveness of sins,</dd><br><dd>the resurrection of the body,</dd><br><dd>and the life everlasting. Amen.</dd><br></dl><br></dd><br></dl><br><br><h3>The Apostles' Creed Prayer in the United Methodist Church</h3><br><br>The Apostles' Creed is usually taken from #881 in the United Methodist Hymnal:<br><br><dl><br><dd>I believe in God the Father Almighty,</dd><br><dd>maker of heaven and earth;</dd><br><dd>And in Jesus Christ his only Son our Lord:</dd><br><dd>who was conceived by the Holy Spirit,</dd><br><dd>born of the Virgin Mary,</dd><br><dd>suffered under Pontius Pilate,</dd><br><dd>was crucified, dead, and buried;</dd><br><dd>the third day he rose from the dead;</dd><br><dd>he ascended into heaven,</dd><br><dd>and sitteth at the right hand of God the Father Almighty;</dd><br><dd>from thence he shall come to judge the quick and the dead.</dd><br><dd>I believe in the Holy Spirit,</dd><br><dd>the holy catholic church,</dd><br><dd>the communion of saints,</dd><br><dd>the forgiveness of sins,</dd><br><dd>the resurrection of the body,</dd><br><dd>and the life everlasting. Amen.</dd><br></dl><br><br><h2>The Apostles' Creed Prayer in Latin</h2><br><br>In Latin, the Apostles' Creed is called either Symbolum Apostolorum or Symbolum Apostolicum.<br><br><dl><br><dd>Credo in Deum Patrem omnipotentem, Creatorem caeli et terrae,</dd><br><dd>et in Iesum Christum, Filium Eius unicum, Dominum nostrum,</dd><br><dd>qui conceptus est de Spiritu Sancto, natus ex Maria Virgine,</dd><br><dd>passus sub Pontio Pilato, crucifixus, mortuus, et sepultus,</dd><br><dd>descendit ad ínferos, tertia die resurrexit a mortuis,</dd><br><dd>ascendit ad caelos, sedet ad dexteram Patris omnipotentis,</dd><br><dd>inde venturus est iudicare vivos et mortuos.</dd><br><dd>Credo in Spiritum Sanctum,</dd><br><dd>sanctam Ecclesiam catholicam, sanctorum communionem,</dd><br><dd>remissionem peccatorum,</dd><br><dd>carnis resurrectionem,</dd><br><dd>vitam aeternam.</dd><br><dd>Amen.</dd><br></dl><br><br><h2 id="usage">Usage</h2><br><br>The Apostles' Creed is a basic creed of traditional Christian belief. So, you can use it to meditate on the points of Christian doctrine. The different articles can be used to meditate on. What does each one mean for you? How does it impact you today?<br><br><ol><br><li>Do you believe in God the Father? What is your relationship like with Him? How could you invite Him into your life even more?<br><br>God the Father is the Being part of God, and His quality is truth. He has made <em>true</em> all of creation, including your soul.</li><br><li>Do you believe in Jesus? How is your relationship with Him? How has He impacted your life?<br><br>The Son is the knowing part of God. God knows Himself infinitely. His quality is power, and the Bible says all power was given to the Son. Knowing oneself brings all power. We are called to live as He did, and must know ourselves as well.</li><br><li>Do you believe that He was conceived by the Holy Spirit? What does this mean about Jesus?<br><br>If Jesus is knowledge, the Holy Spirit is love. Knowledge conceived by love is truly the most powerful. Are your actions conceived by love?</li><br><li>Jesus suffered and died.<br><br>How do you respond to suffering in your own life? Does it overwhelm you and disturb your peace, or do you conquer it?</li><br><li>After three days, Jesus rose again. He conquered His suffering and was given all life in its fullness.<br><br>Have you conquered your darkness, and been resurrected to eternal life in truth?</li><br><li>Jesus reigns with the Father.<br><br>If you are able to conquer your darkness, and learn your true nature, you will have all power in love.</li><br><li>Jesus will come again to judge.<br><br>Will you be judged to have darkness within you? You may find that you will be released when you are able to stop judging yourself so harshly.</li><br><li>Do you believe in the Holy Spirit?<br><br>You must accept the Holy Spirit, the personification of love, into your life. Only then can you be whole.</li><br><li>Do you allow yourself to be united with the community of believers, the body of Christ? You are not on this journey alone.</li><br><li>Have you forgiven others? Have you forgiven yourself? Your sins are forgiven when you have forgiven yourself, and released your guilt.</li><br><li>YOu shall be resurrected to eternal life. This is only when you have been forgiven, and have forgiven yourself. You will be filled with God's life and God's love.</li><br><li>You will possess eternal life. this is the reward of those who follow God, and all will eventually have it. Eternal life is what is given to you, and what you give to all things through the way you live your physical life. It is God's gift to you.</li><br></ol><br><br>As you can see, the Apostles' Creed can be split into separate points that you can apply to your own life, and evaluate your own spirituality, whether you are Christian or not.<br><br>Note that I'm really only familiar with the Apostles' Creed prayer in Catholicism. If I've gotten some information wrong, or missed anything, please let me know in the comments.<br>
